 
Updated on May 12, 2016 8:07 pm
Bollywood star Mallika Sherawat, whose film "Time Raiders" has been selected for the 69th Cannes Film Festival, stunned one and all at the red carpet of the gala's opening ceremony.
(Source: Photo posted in Twitter by Mallika Sherawat)
Mallika wore an off-shoulder Georges Hobeika gown which she paired with a diamond neckpiece from Maison Mellerio for the opening ceremony which was held on Wednesday evening.
Sharing her picture on Twitter she wrote: "Thank you @GeorgesHobeika for this stunning gown,diamonds by @Mellerio, hair by @dessange and make up by @Dior."
(Source: Photo posted in Twitter by Mallika Sherawat)
Mallika Sherawat's gown had golden embellishments with a blue-coloured trail.
She took to Twitter to thank everyone for making her red carpet appearance a successful one.
She wrote: "Thank you all for making my red carpet opening ceremony such a great success!
#Cannes2016 @Festival_Cannes."
(Source: Photo posted in Twitter by Mallika Sherawat)
Minutes before walking the red carpet, Mallika was seen intearcting with French media persons.
She wrote: "Minutes before the red carpet @France3tv @GeorgesHobeika #Cannes2016 #CannesFilmFestival #OpeningCeremony."
(Source: Photo posted in Twitter by Mallika Sherawat)
Mallika Sherawat also posed for photographs at the photocall of her film Time Raiders.
: "Photocall for my international film #timeraiders wearing@Pucci @Festival_Cannes #cannesfilmfestival2016."
(Source: Photo posted in Twitter by Mallika Sherawat)
Dressed in red gown, Mallika has now left for the press conference for her upcoming international film Time Raiders.
Sharing her picture from her escort car she wrote: "On my way to the press conference for my upcoming international film #timeraiders wearing @dolcegabbana."
(Source: Photo posted in Twitter by Mallika Sherawat)
